HEADWORD: Saccharic
<hw>Sac*char"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or obtained from, saccharine substances;
specifically, designating an acid obtained, as a white amorphous gummy
mass, by the oxidation of mannite, glucose, sucrose, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sacchariferous</ent>⟦br⟧
